==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Story-teller
<hw>Sto"ry-tell`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who tells stories; a narrator of anecdotes,incidents, or fictitious
tales; <as>as, an amusing <ex>story-teller</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An historian; -- in contempt.</def>
<rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A euphemism or child's word for ⟦ldquo⟧a
liar.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Story-telling</ent>⟦br⟧
